Exercise 7: Get the first word from your string using indexes. Use the upper function to transform the letters into uppercase. Create a new string that takes the uppercase word and the rest of the original string.

first_word = string_example[:4]
upper_word = first_word.upper()
new_string = f'{upper_word}{string_example[4:]}'

Exercise 8: Use string interpolation to print out a sentence that contains your number variable.

# ACLARACION: Este ejercicio lo puedo hacer de tres formas distintas

# Método 1

new_sentence = f'The probability of precipitation today is {number_example}'

# Método 2 usando format

new_sentence = 'The probability of precipitation today is {0}'.format(number_example)

# Método 3 convirtiendo el número en string

new_sentence = 'The probability of precipitation today is ' + str(number_example)


Exercise 9: Print “hello world”.

print('hello world')
